ant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Normandie","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Alain, Serge, Adrien, Andre, Aurore, Celine, Clovis, Emile, Gaetan, Gilles, Laurier.","French: from a diminutive of   Normand  . Compare   Normandy  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Normand","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Gaston, Andre, Laurent, Marcel, Pierre, Amie, Donat, Emile, Herve, Jacques, Jean Noel, Jean-Michel.","French and Breton (mainly Finistère; also <b>Le Normand</b>): habitational name for someone from Normandy, a region in northern France (see   Norman  ). Compare   Lenormand  .","Scottish (Fife): variant of   Norman  ."]},{"name":"Normandy","meanings":["English: habitational name from Normandy in northern France. This surname is now rare in Britain.","Americanized form of French   Normandin  ."]}]},{"name":"Orence","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Americanized form of German   Lorenz   or   Lorentz  , and of Polish, Czech, Slovak, Croatian, and Slovenian   Lorenc  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Lorenz","meanings":["Variant of   Laurenz ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705182,"age":2,"year":"1066","julianDay":2110409,"title":"Battle of Hastings","description":"Battle of Hastings was fought between the Norman-French army and the battle-wary English army on October 14, 1066. Duke William of Normandy believed he was the rightful king rather than Harold, who had been crowned king several months earlier. Harold was killed in battle and William was crowned king on Christmas Day 1066.","url":"https://www.english-heritage.org.uk/learn/1066-and-the-norman-conquest/what-happened-battle-hastings/","urlTitle":"English Heritage - Battle of Hastings","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705183,"age":22,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Orence De Normandie was born about 1064, in Old Basing, Hampshire, England, her father, Normandie, was 21 and her mother, Mrs. Normandie, was 16. She married Hugh de Porter Jr in 1080. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. She died about 1092, in her hometown, at the age of 30, and was buried in England."},"et":{"about 1064–about 1092":"umbes 1064–umbes 1092","1064–1092":"1064–1092","1051–1096":"1051–1096","1080–1153":"1080–1153","1080–Female":"1080–Surnud","1081–Female":"1081–Surnud","1082–Male":"1082–Surnud","1045–Male":"1045–Surnud","1050–Female":"1050–Surnud","1080":"1080","about 1082":"umbes 1082","after 1080":"pärast 1080","about 1081":"umbes 1081","about 1092":"umbes 1092","1066":"1066","1153":"1153","1086":"1086","1064":"1064","1096":"1096","1051":"1051","1050":"1050","1082":"1082","1092":"1092","1081":"1081","1045":"1045","about 1064":"umbes 1064","about Old Basing, Hampshire, England":"Old Basing, Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hampshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Old Basing, Hampshire, England":"Old Basing, Hampshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1064–about 1092":"noin 1064–noin 1092","1064–1092":"1064–1092","1051–1096":"1051–1096","1080–1153":"1080–1153","1080–Female":"1080–Kuollut","1081–Femal